				<row> 
				  <entry colname="col1"> 
					 <p outputclass="head"> 
						<b>Getting Access</b> 
					 </p> 
					 <ul id="ul_47C012F6AB3E4B73BA357027F4D15369"> 
						<li id="li_2364E5490452427981008D3F859837F8"><xref
						  href="access.xml#concept_04341546E8B44CDF833F9DDF351A50B9" format="dita"
						  scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Accessing the Marketing Cloud?></xref> 
						  <p>Learn about joining the 
							 <keyword>Marketing Cloud</keyword>, logging in, linking
							 accounts, and managing organizations. (Admins: Provisioning is a prerequisite.)
							 
						  </p> 
						</li> 
						<li id="li_1310DC29A84C490A9AF919DFA36A5CAB"> 
						  <xref
							href="admin_getting_started.xml#concept_A9A190B372C5450CA53D60431D362143"
							format="dita" scope="local"> Administrators</xref> 
						  <p>Learn about provisioning your company and becoming an
							 administrator in the 
							 <keyword>Marketing Cloud</keyword>. 
						  </p> 
						</li> 
						<li id="li_E106C1467B2F42DFA1F870B4C353085F"><xref
						  href="faq.xml#concept_13219B4E51784577B6FF78AAA203DE91" format="dita"
						  scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Frequently Asked Questions - Marketing Cloud?></xref>
						  
						  <p>Questions and answers about the 
							 <keyword>Marketing Cloud</keyword>. (Recommended for
							 administrators.) 
						  </p> 
						</li> 
						<li id="li_F7DEBE7B1DF3491D86E1DA64554D5361"> 
						  <xref
							href="https://developer.omniture.com/en_US/documentation/authentication/auth-overview"
							format="https" scope="external">Developers</xref> 
						  <p>Learn how to authenticate using OAuth2 when calling the
							 web services APIs. 
						  </p> 
						</li> 
					 </ul> 
					 <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="head"> 
						<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Using the Marketing Cloud</b> 
					 </p> 
					 <ul id="ul_04ED8CEEE1A745A5935656140584D0FE"> 
						<li id="li_7269A959934F4C3E9F13B9719D51F93E"> 
						  <xref
							href="faq.xml#concept_13219B4E51784577B6FF78AAA203DE91" format="dita"
							scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Frequently Asked Questions - Marketing Cloud?></xref>
						  
						  <p>Admins - get answers to common questions about the 
							 <keyword>Marketing Cloud</keyword>. 
						  </p> 
						</li> 
						<li id="li_DE5978CB535D4BB299A428B791799E86"> 
						  <xref
							href="feed.xml#concept_9256B8768A294009A777282DD8719213" format="dita"
							scope="local">Feeds</xref> 
						  <p>A 
							 <term>Feed</term> is where you see all that is happening.
							 You can monitor the latest changes in your assets and campaigns, and navigate
							 to a more detailed view in an individual 
							 <xref
							  href="cards.xml#concept_0A2472B530E04930BCE5CC23A8BEF9E0" format="dita"
							  scope="local">card</xref>. 
						  </p> 
						</li> 
						<li id="li_E06CDD18D9564DD097FE2F0A39FC82BB"> 
						  <xref
							href="boards.xml#concept_52E7E7B015D14E2C852D9618CF76860F" format="dita"
							scope="local">Boards</xref> 
						  <p>A 
							 <term>Board</term> is where you collaborate around
							 marketing campaigns, and 
							 <xref
							  href="t_share_analytics_usecase.xml#task_F7AE118436FA4E01BFAF79B485482820"
							  format="dita" scope="local">share</xref> reports or a creative asset. 
						  </p> 
						</li> 
					 </ul> 
					 <p outputclass="head"> 
						<b>Release Notes &amp; Solution Help</b> 
					 </p> 
					 <ul id="ul_723B64B3B36E423F92D204DB6ADC431E"> 
						<li id="li_2A8575F36DFD495A853CB174D4D095AC"> 
						  <xref
							href="release_notes.xml#concept_F5C9FF69A5B44395BB5FA0552F4E9175" format="dita"
							scope="local"> <?xm-replace_text Release Notes?>
						  </xref> 
						  <p>Learn about known issues and what's new in the Marketing
							 Cloud interface. 
						  </p> 
						</li> 
						<li id="li_D9C1262A714A46F0ADAD05A984127AC9"> 
						  <xref
						  href="https://marketing.adobe.com/resources/help/en_US/whatsnew/"
						  format="https" scope="external">Release Notes - All Solutions</xref> 
						  <p>Learn about this month's new features and fixes for all
							 Marketing Cloud solutions. 
						  </p> 
						</li> 
						<li id="li_B3B35F1E4D104B7397A35DC956D190F9"> 
						  <xref
							href="https://marketing.adobe.com/resources/help/en_US/home/" format="https"
							scope="external">Product Documentation Home</xref> 
						  <p>Search and browse for help across all product
							 documentation topics. 
						  </p> 
						</li> 
					 </ul> 
				  </entry> 
				  <entry colname="col2"> 
					 <p class="- topic/p " outputclass="head"> 
						<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Core Services Help</b> 
					 </p> 
					 <ul id="ul_B16BCA80511C4F7AB5A34524988227DD"> 
						<li id="li_DF5D71FCFEAB4154A4C1FDEF70AA0A9C"> 
						  <xref
							href="audiences.xml#concept_F31D8B62FD5144E181979C3A300336A5" format="dita"
							scope="local"> <?xm-replace_text Audiences Services - Master Marketing Profile?>
						  </xref> 
						  <p>Implement and start using shared audiences. Creating and
							 managing audiences is similar to creating and using segments, with the addition
							 of the ability to share them to 
							 <keyword>Marketing Cloud</keyword> solutions. 
						  </p> 
						</li> 
						<li id="li_7FC28F9BA24A4007B0C396C376C214C6"> 
						  <xref
							href="https://marketing.adobe.com/resources/help/en_US/dtm/" format="https"
							scope="external">Dynamic Tag Management</xref>: Adobe now offers dynamic tag
						  management, the market-leading solution that reduces the need for IT resources
						  and allows you to quickly manage tags and distribute data. It is part of 
						  <keyword>Adobe Marketing Cloud</keyword>, and available to
						  customers at no additional cost. 
						</li> 
						<li id="li_38CCE4019F4B4A1991DDE1F5D918E681"> 
						  <xref
							href="https://marketing.adobe.com/resources/help/en_US/mobile/" format="https"
							scope="external">Adobe Mobile Services</xref>: Bring together mobile marketing
						  capabilities for mobile applications from across the Marketing Cloud. 
						</li> 
					 </ul> 
					 <p outputclass="head"> 
						<b>News</b> 
					 </p> 
					 <ul id="ul_45F8DAB6A2FE45459583E7F312B29102"> 
						<li id="li_90EA11A968BD4352A738AD33EF199984"> 
						  <xref
							href="https://marketing.adobe.com/resources/help/en_US/tnt/help/"
							format="https" scope="external">Adobe Testing and Targeting Classic</xref> is
						  now accessible from the Marketing Cloud interface. You can visually create and
						  manage A/B tests and rules-based targeting activities, and connect to the 
						  <keyword>Adobe Marketing Cloud</keyword>. 
						  <keyword>Target Classic</keyword> offers a simplified
						  implementation strategy with your digital properties: just a single line of
						  code on each page manages all communication required between your site and 
						  <keyword>Adobe Target</keyword>. 
						</li> 
					 </ul> 
